<debugging>  
When debugging, only make code changes if you are confident they will address the actual problem. Otherwise, follow these best practices:  
1. Identify and address the root cause of the issue rather than just fixing superficial symptoms.  
2. Add descriptive logging statements and error messages to trace the execution flow and inspect important variables or states.  
3. Write small test cases or use interactive exploration (e.g., in a Python REPL) to isolate the problem and verify that the fix addresses it without introducing regressions.  
